          <p>This review was written and published by theStacc, a competing product. We have a commercial interest as an alternative. Every feature claim and price was verified against Serpstat's public pricing page as of Q2 2026. Where we are biased, we say so.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Want traffic, not another tool to learn?</h4>
            <p>Get a <strong>free SEO audit</strong> in 24 hours. We will show you the keywords you are missing, the technical fixes that move the needle, and your competitors content gaps — no sales call, no obligation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">Get my free audit <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">24-hour delivery · No card</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="vs-stacc">theStacc vs Serpstat — where we are honestly better (and worse)</h2>
        <p>We wrote this review. We compete. Read the comparison first so you can weigh everything that follows.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Serpstat</th><th>theStacc</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Starting price</td><td>$69/mo</td><td class="cell-yes">$99/mo</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Articles written for you</td><td class="cell-no">No — research tool only</td><td class="cell-yes">30 / month</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Auto-publishes to your CMS</td><td class="cell-no">No</td><td class="cell-yes">WordPress · Webflow · Ghost</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Google Business Profile posts</td><td class="cell-no">Not included</td><td class="cell-yes">30 GBP posts / month</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Social media posts (IG, LI, X, FB)</td><td class="cell-no">Not included</td><td class="cell-yes">30 posts / month</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Done-for-you (no workflow to run)</td><td class="cell-no">DIY — you run everything</td><td class="cell-yes">Fully managed</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Real monthly cost (tool + writers + ops)</strong></td><td>$5,834+/mo</td><td><strong>$99 flat</strong></td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p><strong>Where Serpstat wins:</strong> if your job is research, competitive analysis, or running a multi-client agency — Serpstat earns its keep. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if your job is growing organic traffic without hiring a content team. Pick by the job, not the brand.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Serpstat?</h2>
        <p>Serpstat is an all-in-one SEO platform built around keyword research, competitor analysis, site auditing, backlink checking, and rank tracking. The name combines 'SERP' (Search Engine Results Page) + 'stat' (statistics) — which tells you the core focus: measuring and analysing search visibility data.</p>

        <p>Serpstat covers billions of keywords across <strong>230+ regional Google databases</strong>. The backlink index tracks hundreds of billions of links. These numbers are smaller than Semrush and Ahrefs but substantial for most real-world use cases. The platform's user base is concentrated in Eastern Europe, CIS countries, and North America.</p>

        <p>What Serpstat is <em>not</em>: a content creation platform, an automated publishing system, or a done-for-you SEO service. It finds keywords, analyses competitors, audits sites, tracks rankings, and checks backlinks. You still write every article, optimise every page, and publish everything manually.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">Company background</div>
          <p>2013, started as an internal tool at <strong>Netpeak, a digital marketing agency in Odesa, Ukraine</strong>. Oleg Salamaha created the original product. Artem Borodatyuk drove expansion. Launched as standalone SaaS in 2015. Raised $250K in seed funding in 2014 from Digital Future and Netpeak Group. Has remained independent and profitable. Team operates primarily from Ukraine.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">Serpstat features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is broad. Here is what actually matters in daily use, broken down by module.</p>

        <h3>1. Keyword Research</h3>
        <p>Serpstat's strongest module. Volume, difficulty, CPC, related keywords, questions, and 'People Also Ask' variations. Includes <strong>10 years of historical search volume data</strong> and AI-powered semantic clustering. Tree View for hierarchical content planning is unique to Serpstat.</p>

        <h3>2. Competitor Research</h3>
        <p>Domain analysis surfaces a competitor's top keywords, traffic estimates, paid keywords, and ad copy. The Missing Keywords report shows keywords competitors rank for that you do not — your highest-leverage content opportunities.</p>

        <h3>3. Site Audit</h3>
        <p>100+ technical SEO checks. Crawl depth, internal linking, hreflang, schema validation, Core Web Vitals. Crawler is fast and configurable. Less granular than Semrush (140+) but catches the same critical issues.</p>

        <h3>4. Backlink Analysis</h3>
        <p>Hundreds of billions of links indexed. Toxic backlink detection, disavow file generation, lost-link alerts. Index is smaller and less fresh than Ahrefs, but adequate for monitoring your own profile and assessing competitor link strategy.</p>

        <h3>5. Rank Tracking</h3>
        <p>Daily desktop, mobile, and local rank tracking across 230+ regional Google databases. SERP feature tracking and competitor comparison included. White-label reports on Agency plan.</p>

        <h3>6. AI Tools</h3>
        <p>Recent additions include AI content scoring and AI keyword generation. Useful for first-draft research; not a replacement for dedicated content optimisation tools like Surfer or Clearscope.</p>

        <h3>7. Reporting</h3>
        <p>Customisable PDF reports, scheduled email delivery, and white-label branding on Agency. Looker Studio connector included.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">Serpstat pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>Serpstat publishes pricing. Most reviews quote the sticker. We will quote the <em>full</em> cost — sticker plus everything you have to bolt on to actually publish content.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Monthly</th><th>Annual / mo</th><th>What you get</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Individual</strong></td><td>$69</td><td>$55</td><td>1 user · 4,000 keywords/day · 15K results/report</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Team</strong></td><td>$149</td><td>$119</td><td>5 users · 6,000 keywords/day · API access</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Agency</strong></td><td>$499</td><td>$399</td><td>20 users · 12,000 keywords/day · white-label</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>Annual billing typically saves 15–33%. Additional users and add-on modules cost extra. A free trial or money-back guarantee is available — verify the current terms on the official pricing page before purchase.</p>

        <h3>The real monthly cost most reviews skip</h3>
        <p>Serpstat hands you the data. It does not write, optimise, or publish anything. To actually run SEO with Serpstat's intelligence, here is the real monthly math:</p>

        <div class="cost-calc">
